From Default Ubuntu Server Install (20.04)

As sudo user:

> Install Node.js v15.x

**Note; curling to bash is a horrible idea. Make 100% sure you are comfortable and knowledgeable about the code being run**

curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_15.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

> discord.js [used for interfacting with discord]
sudo npm install discord.js @discordjs/opus

> ytdl [youtubedownload, used for reading media from youtube]
sudo npm install ytdl
sudo npm install ytdl-core

> ffmpeg [used for media transcribing
sudo npm i ffmpeg-static

> update the sensitive.js file with your discord token
> run the bot
node disbot.js
